01:36:12.200 --> 01:36:17.200
So if you are overheated
to a point where, you know,

01:36:17.600 --> 01:36:18.960
you're getting up past 102

01:36:18.960 --> 01:36:20.860
or 103, it's going to vary depending

01:36:20.860 --> 01:36:24.230
on person to person and
certainly age, you know, kids,

01:36:24.230 --> 01:36:25.990
some people think can
tolerate higher levels

01:36:25.990 --> 01:36:27.510
of fever than adults, but look,

01:36:27.510 --> 01:36:29.690
you always want to be cautious
about heating up the brain

01:36:29.690 --> 01:36:31.350
too much, because once
those neurons are gone,

01:36:31.350 --> 01:36:33.680
they do not come back and
neurons do not do well

01:36:33.680 --> 01:36:35.370
in very high temperatures.

01:36:35.370 --> 01:36:37.570
Once your body temperature
starts getting up

01:36:38.420 --> 01:36:41.110
to 102, 103, certainly 104,

01:36:41.110 --> 01:36:43.500
you are starting to enter
serious danger zone.

01:36:43.500 --> 01:36:46.570
This can happen through
exercise in hot environments

01:36:46.570 --> 01:36:49.250
or an inability to escape heat

01:36:49.250 --> 01:36:51.251
because you don't have covering

01:36:51.251 --> 01:36:53.570
or adequate ventilation or cooling.

01:36:53.570 --> 01:36:55.670
It can also be because of excessive fever,

01:36:55.670 --> 01:36:56.970
for whatever reason.

01:36:56.970 --> 01:36:59.750
A lot of people think the way
to deal with this is to put a

01:36:59.750 --> 01:37:04.343
