01:37:08.170 --> 01:37:10.690
who's at Stanford School of Medicine,

01:37:10.690 --> 01:37:12.680
and he's on the undergraduate side

01:37:12.680 --> 01:37:14.900
of the campus as well, runs a biology lab.

01:37:14.900 --> 01:37:17.360
He's a world expert in thermal regulation.

01:37:17.360 --> 01:37:20.270
It's very clear that
that's the wrong response

01:37:20.270 --> 01:37:21.733
to try and cool off the body.

01:37:22.880 --> 01:37:26.770
If you put a cold towel
or you put an ice pack

01:37:26.770 --> 01:37:29.340
on the back of the neck, what
you effectively do is cool

01:37:29.340 --> 01:37:31.310
the blood that's going to the brain.

01:37:31.310 --> 01:37:33.030
And if you do that,

01:37:33.030 --> 01:37:36.980
then your brain will react
by turning up the crank

01:37:36.980 --> 01:37:40.550
in so to speak on the neurons
in the pre optic area,

01:37:40.550 --> 01:37:43.100
and will heat you up further
and can cook your brain

01:37:43.100 --> 01:37:44.740
and organs further.

01:37:44.740 --> 01:37:46.760
So what you want to do is, as I've talked

01:37:46.760 --> 01:37:50.540
about before, you want to
cool the bottoms of the feet,

01:37:50.540 --> 01:37:53.660
the palms of the hands and
the upper part of the face.

01:37:53.660 --> 01:37:55.480
And I'm not going to
go into all the details

01:37:55.480 --> 01:37:57.140
as to why you want to do that right now,

01:37:57.140 --> 01:37:58.820
but those are the
locations you want to cool.

01:37:58.820 --> 01:38:00.890
Now you can also cool
the rest of the body,

01:38:00.890 --> 01:38:03.290
but it's not okay to just
stay under the covers

01:38:03.290 --> 01:38:06.380
and just cool, you know, the
neck or something like that.

01:38:06.380 --> 01:38:09.220
You really want to try
and create a systemic

01:38:09.220 --> 01:38:12.160
or whole body cooling, if the
goal is to bring fever down,

01:38:12.160 --> 01:38:14.100
but in many cases, fever is adaptive.

01:38:14.100 --> 01:38:17.800
And so taking a non-steroid
anti-inflammatory drugs

01:38:19.120 --> 01:38:20.230
