that pyrogen, it's sometimes called,

01:38:29.520 --> 01:38:30.950
a pyrogen is a substance
that causes fever,

01:38:30.950 --> 01:38:35.553
think pyro, think fire, think
pyromaniacs, think pyro,

01:38:36.520 --> 01:38:40.440
those pyrogens can survive at
moderate to low temperatures,

01:38:40.440 --> 01:38:41.880
and they can't survive
at high temperatures.

01:38:41.880 --> 01:38:44.457
So the fever is an adaptive
mechanism and the OVLT,

01:38:44.457 --> 01:38:48.780
and the sensing of your
chemistry is how the OVLT,

01:38:48.780 --> 01:38:51.640
organum vasculosum of the
lateral terminalis does that.

01:38:51.640 --> 01:38:55.250
So we've talked about sensing lung volume,

